from math import *
def tub(n):
    if(n<2):return 0
    if((n%2==0 and n!=2) or (n%3==0 and n!=3) or (n%5==0 and n!=5) or (n%7==0 and n!=7)):return 0
    for i in range(11,int(sqrt(n))+1,2):
        if n%i==0:return 0
    return 1
def fib(n):
    F = [[1, 1],
         [1, 0]]
    if (n == 0):
        return 0
    power(F, n - 1)
    return F[0][0]
def multiply(F, M):
    x = (F[0][0] * M[0][0] +
         F[0][1] * M[1][0])
    y = (F[0][0] * M[0][1] +
         F[0][1] * M[1][1])
    z = (F[1][0] * M[0][0] +
         F[1][1] * M[1][0])
    w = (F[1][0] * M[0][1] +
         F[1][1] * M[1][1])
    F[0][0] = x
    F[0][1] = y
    F[1][0] = z
    F[1][1] = w
def power(F, n):
    if (n == 0 or n == 1):
        return;
    M = [[1, 1],
         [1, 0]];
    power(F, n // 2)
    multiply(F, F)
    if (n % 2 != 0):
        multiply(F, M)
